The paper deals with the problem of compactly representing and querying graph search trees, which is a fundamental data structure in graph algorithms. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also involves partitioning techniques, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and divide-and-conquer algorithms (cs.DC). Finally, the paper applies the techniques to index other graph structures, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT).
